songs.description: Likely, this version appeared for me on Apple Music near the end of last year. A big part of this year’s musical diet and therefore the opening track.
Of all the songs in Archie Shepp’s [Goin’ Home](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goin%27_Home_(Archie_Shepp_and_Horace_Parlan_album)), this one made the top this year.
Excited to see others losing their minds over this album, actually, I am happy to lose it together.
I am not into the Grateful Dead. Maybe one day that will change – this is as remote as we’d get this year.

The album to which this song belongs to was being played while shopping at [A-1 Records](https://www.a-1recordshop.com) (of course...). It makes me think of something out of [Midnight Cowboy](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q-W_rye752o) or [A Clockwork Orange](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8TTFSU0Kqng).
This was a discovery. You can hear about it [here](https://youtu.be/Eg-PCEtmgaY?t=338).
Of all versions… and one of my played songs this year.
